{"questionId":"21879080","questionHtml":"<p>Find the <math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mi>x</mi></math>-coordinate of point <math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mi mathvariant=\"normal\">A</mi></math> and the <math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mi>x</mi></math>-coordinate of point <math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mi mathvariant=\"normal\">C</mi></math>.</p>","markschemeHtml":"<p>recognising&nbsp;<math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mi>cos</mi><mo> </mo><mi>x</mi><mo>=</mo><mn>2</mn><mo> </mo><mi>sin</mi><mo> </mo><mi>x</mi><mo> </mo><mi>cos</mi><mo> </mo><mi>x</mi></math>&nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp;&nbsp;<strong><em>(M1)</em></strong></p>\n<p><math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mfenced><mrow><mi>cos</mi><mo> </mo><mi>x</mi><mo>≠</mo><mn>0</mn></mrow></mfenced></math>&nbsp;so&nbsp;<math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mi>sin</mi><mo> </mo><mi>x</mi><mo>=</mo><mfrac><mn>1</mn><mn>2</mn></mfrac></math>&nbsp; &nbsp;OR&nbsp; &nbsp;one correct value (accept degrees)&nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp;&nbsp;<strong><em>(A1)</em></strong></p>\n<p><math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mi>x</mi></math>-coordinates&nbsp;<math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mfrac><mi mathvariant=\"normal\">π</mi><mn>6</mn></mfrac></math>&nbsp;and&nbsp;<math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mfrac><mrow><mn>5</mn><mi mathvariant=\"normal\">π</mi></mrow><mn>6</mn></mfrac></math>&nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp;&nbsp;<strong><em>A1</em></strong></p>\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\n<p><strong>Note:</strong> Award <em><strong>(M1)(A1)A0</strong></em> for solutions of <math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mn>30</mn><mo>°</mo></math> and <math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mn>150</mn><mo>°</mo></math>.</p>\n<p style=\"text-align:right;\"><em><strong>[3 marks]</strong></em></p>","meta":{"questionId":"21879080","referenceCode":"24M.1